text: Noyers-Missy was a short-lived commune. It is found in the region Normandy in the Calvados department in the northwest of France. The municipality was created on 1 January 2016 and consists of the former communes of Noyers-Bocage (the seat) and Missy.Arrêté préfectoral 9 December 2015 On 1 January 2017, it was merged into the new commune of Val d'Arry.Arrêté préfectoral 8 September 2016 == References == Category:2016 establishments in France Category:21st- century disestablishments in France Category:2017 disestablishments in Europe Category:Former communes in Calvados Category:2010s disestablishments in France
